
# ğŸ”· Cisco OSPF Protocol Configuration Guide

This README provides a basic setup for OSPF (Open Shortest Path First) on Cisco routers.

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Basic Router Setup

```bash
enable
configure terminal
hostname ROUTER_NAME
no ip domain-lookup
```

---

## ğŸŒ Interface IP Configuration

```bash
interface FastEthernet0/0
  ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
  no shutdown
exit

interface FastEthernet0/1
  ip address 10.0.0.1 255.255.255.0
  no shutdown
exit
```

---

## ğŸ” OSPF Configuration

```bash
router ospf 1
  network 192.168.1.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
  network 10.0.0.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
exit
```

---

## ğŸ” Verification Commands

```bash
show ip protocols
show ip ospf neighbor
show ip route ospf
show running-config
```

---

## ğŸ’¾ Save Configuration

```bash
copy running-config startup-config
```

---

## ğŸ§  Notes

- OSPF is a link-state protocol and uses areas (Area 0 is backbone).
- Use wildcard masks in the `network` command.
- OSPF is more scalable than RIP.

